<p>The <code>white</code> function normalizes whitespace - collapses multiple spaces to a single space.</p>

<h2>Basic Usage</h2>
<pre>{open}'hello    world' | white{close}</pre>
<p>Result: <b>{'hello    world' | white}</b></p>

<h2>Clean User Input</h2>
<pre>{open}'  multiple   spaces   here  ' | trim | white{close}</pre>
<p>Cleaned: <b>{'  multiple   spaces   here  ' | trim | white}</b></p>

<h2>Chained Examples</h2>
<pre>{open}'  HELLO    WORLD  ' | trim | white | lower | capitalize{close}</pre>
<p>Full cleanup: <b>{'  HELLO    WORLD  ' | trim | white | lower | capitalize}</b></p>

<pre>{open}'John     Doe' | white | before(' ') | left(1){close}. {open}'John     Doe' | white | after(' '){close}</pre>
<p>Abbreviated: <b>{'John     Doe' | white | before(' ') | left(1)}. {'John     Doe' | white | after(' ')}</b></p>

<h2>Complex Chain</h2>
<pre>{open}'Product:    Widget    XL    Blue' | white | after(': ') | replace(' ', '-') | lower{close}</pre>
<p>Product slug: <b>{'Product:    Widget    XL    Blue' | white | after(': ') | replace(' ', '-') | lower}</b></p>
